===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}}. The upper part and the lower part of the character, on the basis of the original versions, can be unified into {{m|zh|合}} (two open mouths) with a food container in the middle; this character means both "bring together" (e.g., bring together people to discuss, putting a lid on a vessel) and "close, shut". The top of the character resembles {{m|zh|食}}, but it's connected to another mouth at the bottom of the character. The food container could be a {{m|zh|膾}}, an ancient container for raw fish and finely minced/chopped meat.

===Etymology===
Most of the pronunciations are ultimately cognate, derived from a root meaning "to join, to come together ~ to meet, to gather ~ to match, to fit ~ to understand". Perhaps related to {{och-l|合|to match}} ~ {{och-l|蓋|lid}}.

However, Min Nan ''ē'' instead derives from {{och-l|解|to understand}} ({{zh-ref|Yang, 2001}}).

